    991          /**
    992           *    @brief    This method writes data from ‘source’ (buffer address mentioned by the Application) to\n
    993           *              the ‘destination’ (Transmitter FIFO) as per the size mentioned to the specific Uart\n
    994           *              and also returns the response for the write operation.
    995           *    @details  The data in the Transmitter FIFO is sent to other Uart node through the\n
    996           *              specified Uart COM port whenever the Transmitter is free.\n
    997           *              Before writing into the Transmitter FIFO check for the FIFO availability using Uart__GetStatus() API\n
    998           *              to avoid the over writing on the existing data.
    999           *    @param    uart : Defines the Specific Uart COM port.
   1000           *    @param    buf : Indicates the buffer’s address which contains the data to be sent.
   1001           *    @param    size : Defines the number of bytes to be sent.
   1002           *    @return   BOOL_TYPE
   1003           *      @retval TRUE (1): If the data written in the transmission FIFO is successful.
   1004           *      @retval FALSE (0): If data written in the transmission FIFO is failed.
   1005           *
   1006           *    @image    html    Uart__Write.jpg
   1007           */

   \                                 In section .text, align 2, keep-with-next
