   1597          /**
   1598           *    @brief    This method checks the status of the specific Uart.
   1599           *    @details  This method checks the break in, break out signal, transmit and receive FIFO availability for\n
   1600           *              writing and reading, transmit FIFO empty and error status of received frame.
   1601           *    @param    uart : Defines the Specific Uart COM port.
   1602           *    @param    index : Index enumerator defines which status should be checked for specific Uart.
   1603           *
   1604           *    @return   UART_STATUS_BREAK_IN:\n
   1605           *              Response:   TRUE (1) = If it detects the Break signal sent by other node.\n
   1606           *                          FALSE (0) = No break signal is detected.\n
   1607           *              UART_STATUS_BREAK_OUT:\n
   1608           *              Response:   TRUE (1) = A break signal is sent;\n
   1609           *                          FALSE (0) = No break signal is sent;\n
   1610           *              UART_STATUS_TX_EMPTY:\n
   1611           *              Response:   TRUE (1) = The transmission FIFO is empty;\n
   1612           *                          FALSE (0) = The transmission FIFO is not empty;\n
   1613           *              UART_STATUS_TX_AVAILABLE:\n
   1614           *              Response:   The response is the free space in the Transmission FIFO\n
   1615           *                          If the response is 1 means the only one byte is free in the Tx FIFO,\n
   1616           *                          if response is 10 means only 10 bytes are free in the Tx FIFO.\n
   1617           *              UART_STATUS_RX_AVAILABLE:\n
   1618           *              Response:   The amount of bytes available in the Reception FIFO;\n
   1619           *                          If the response is 1 means the only one byte is available to read the Rx FIFO,\n
   1620           *                          If response is 10 means only 10 bytes are available to read the the Rx FIFO.\n
   1621           *              UART_STATUS_ERROR:\n
   1622           *              Response:   TRUE (1) = Error detected (Over run, Framing, Parity or noise_err error)\n
   1623           *                          FALSE (0) = No error detected.
   1624           *
   1625           */

   \                                 In section .text, align 4, keep-with-next
